      "schema:description": "The Guadiana Lower Estuary sampling site is located between 37 13' 15.03\" N, 007 24' 49.86\" W and 37 07' 44.04\" N, 007 24' 06.36\" W, and includes two sampling stations, in the estuary mouth and in the plume (stations G1 and G2, respectively), in a water depth ranging from 5 to 30 m (Figure 1).The Guadiana site is a mesotidal estuary with an average amplitude of 2 m ranging from partially stratified to well-mixed, an average depth of 6,5 m and an area of 22 km2. It can be divided into three sub-areas: upper, middle and lower estuary (Chicharo et al., 2001). The lower estuarine area is influenced by extensive saltmarshes areas and the salinity is usually very close to that of seawater (>20).",
